            {
              "text": "All 7 required code files have been successfully created and tested. Here's a summary of the implementation:\n\n## Created Files\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| **preprocess.py** | Image preprocessing module - downsampling, Gaussian blur, background subtraction, CLAHE enhancement |\n| **coarse_detection.py** | Coarse detection - Canny edge detection, contour analysis, Hough circle detection, combined methods |\n| **fine_detection.py** | Fine detection - radial gradient scanning, dual edge detection strategy, least squares circle fitting |\n| **statistical_analysis.py** | Robust statistical analysis - MAD (Median Absolute Deviation), 3σ principle outlier removal, robust circle fitting |\n| **mask_generation.py** | Mask generation - circular/ring masks, chord detection and adaptive clipping, edge refinement |\n| **main.py** | Main program entry - CLI interface, logging, visualization, complete detection pipeline |\n| **test.py** | Test evaluation module - ground truth loading, error calculation, performance evaluation, report generation |\n\n## Key Features\n\n- **Preprocessing**: Handles 3w×3w images via downsampling (target_size configurable), Gaussian blur for noise reduction, morphological background subtraction\n\n- **Coarse Detection**: Multiple methods (contour-based, Hough circles, image moments), combined mode averages results for robustness\n\n- **Fine Detection**: Radial gradient scanning with 360 rays by default, dual edge detection finds rising edges, RANSAC-style robust fitting\n\n- **Statistical Analysis**: MAD-based outlier detection (1.4826 scaling to match σ), iterative refinement, special point identification (chord midpoints, high intensity, outliers)\n\n- **Mask Generation**: Smooth edges using sigmoid function, chord detection via angular gap analysis, hole filling, edge refinement\n\n- **Performance**: Processing time < 1s for synthetic test image, modular design allows parameter tuning\n\n## Usage Examples\n\n```bash\n# Basic detection\npython main.py input.png -o output.png -m mask.png -j result.json\n\n# With verbose logging\npython main.py input.png -v --num-rays 720 --gradient-threshold 0.05\n\n# Test evaluation\npython test.py -g ground_truth.json -i images/ -r report.txt -j results.json\n```",
              "mediaUrl": null
            }
